Not acceptable.

I visited this restaurant during a lunch break in the area. I placed my order at the counter and sat down at a table. When I received my food packaged to go I thought it was kind of odd (and wasteful) but sat down to eat it. Apparently it was a mistake to dine in because the owner got into a huff. Mind you a few minutes ago she was smiling at me as I interacted with her small daughter as I ordered. Long story short: the owner had a nasty attitude because I dared to dine in and eat my food. There were two other customers dining in so I didn't see the big deal. If you don't want people to dine in either tell them and/or consider if you really need to own and operate a sit down restaurant. The food was mediocre on top of the nasty attitude. This one had a little too much cream.  This is an okay place to eat at, but if you're craving authentic-tasting Thai food, I'd recommend Opart. My last stop in my 55th Street  Thai experience, but now my first choice in go-to yummy deliciousness 💗 The tofu fried rice was seasoned to perfection, delish 🍚! The egg rolls were good and they provided enough sweet n sour sauce in a cup for both of them 🥚. The Thai iced tea was really sweet🍯, but I appreciate that I said not a lot of ice and they didn’t put a lot in 🥛. Nothing is worse than walking home with melting ice in your Thai iced tea and having to drink it watered down lol. Finally I saw they had mango sticky rice and so I ordered it expecting them to say it was out of season but they had it. The rice was good and maybe they should charge extra when it is out of season for them to keep mangos in paper bags to make them ripe rather than sell them unripened. I’ll keep it in the fridge a few days and cross my fingers lol. So far Snail Queen Thai is the only other Thai place with them on the menu, but their mangos are PERFECT. All in all this was really good and I’m likely to make this my go-to local Thai restaurant. I love I can walk to them but plus side they deliver so it’s great 💕

At first I thought someone accidentally poured a bottle of soy sauce on it (which might have been an improvement) but discovered the black liquid was a basically flavorless water. 3. Curry Duck had slightly more duck but still less than 2 ounces. Sauce was less bland than the black sauce, but still unrecognizable as a curry. 4. For what you received it was WAY overpriced. 5.  I was dinning with a companion, the dishes were served separately - which was surprising since both were cold. 6. Only one worker in the dining room, who was pleasant, but often missing. Which leads us to believe that he was the only worker in the restaurant, and was serving food from a steam table that was not on.  7. Conclusion: I know that all restaurants have bad days, and if my only experience there was typical.. this restaurant would be closed.

I go in and wait about 10 minutes before anyone says anything to me...and there were only 2 other people in the restaurant at 5pm. The female waiter came over while I was looking in my purse for my wallet and then walked away without taking my order.  5 minutes later after waiving another waiter down, a man comes over.  I asked him if he had ginger tea, which is not normally advertised on menues but most Thai food places have it by request.  He said no and so I end up choosing the Jasmine tea.  He stood there with a sarcastic look on his face and asked me "is that it".. I said yes, for now.  I swear to you, his face turned red.  He told me that I couldn't just order tea.
